"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-09-parisolympics-hibbert-places-fourth-triple-jump-final\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Jamaica's Jaydon Hibbert came up just short of winning a medal in the men's triple jump at the Olympic Games as he finished fourth with 17.61m (-0.9m/s) behind three Cuban-born jumpers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 26, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9249465905963906, \"rank\": 0.07213238210898823, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 43, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\", \"score\": 0.998420151056087, \"rank\": 0.001582348797649856, \"text\": \"Hibbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hibbert, who competed with a heavily strapped left knee, made a gallant effort but failed to get on the medal podium with a mere three centimetres out of third place.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\", \"score\": 0.998420151056087, \"rank\": 0.001582348797649856, \"text\": \"Hibbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Hibbert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He bypassed his final round effort, a possible indication that he was not fully fit going into the competition.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 19-year-old missed out on a chance of winning his first senior medal last year when he was injured in the final at the World Championships.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During Friday's final he started with a mark of 17.31m (0.3m/s), jumped 17.61m in the second round and the 17.53m (0.0m/s) before fouling on his next two attempts.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spain's Jordan Alejandro Diaz Fortun won with 17.86m (0.1m/s), two centimetres ahead of defending champion Pedro Pitchardo of Portugal-17.84m (0.2m/s) and Andy Diaz Hernandez of Italy was third with a season's best 17.64m (0.7m/s)  -Paul A Reid  Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9991992912162796, \"rank\": 0.0007468384266919091, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 805, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"score\": 0.8764701954312671, \"rank\": 0.11205457915135945, \"text\": \"Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\"}, {\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alejandro_Escovedo\", \"score\": 0.8737034389547794, \"rank\": 0.09769088242369274, \"text\": \"Alejandro\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alejandro_Escovedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alejandro_Escovedo\"}, {\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fortun_(village)\", \"score\": 0.9529505816113166, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fortun\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fortun_(village)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou